communicated by:
ProMED-mail rapporteur Kunihiko Iizuka

[This set of news snippets from the Washington Post covers an array of how responses to COVID-19 vary among different states and different individuals. Some very poignant vignettes are included, description of fear in some individuals, defiant responses by others, some trying to provide guidance and support to individuals struggling to make it through the pandemic, and more. Children to seniors have been affected, as has every single individual by this viral disease, either directly or indirectly. One hopes that should an existing or new variant pose even a graver risk, vaccine makers will be able to respond rapidly as they are currently doing. And further, one hopes the public health infrastructure that has been strengthened by this pandemic will be maintained to battle the next outbreak, which no doubt will come in the future. Trained health care and laboratory personnel are a precious commodity that must be protected. The lessons learned from how this pandemic was handled should be discussed and plans made so mistakes are not repeated. - Mod.LK]

