communicated by:
ProMED
<promed@promedmail.org>

[Data by country, area, or territory for 8 Mar 2021 can be accessed at https://promedmail.org/wp-content/uploads/world-pdf/WHO%20update%208%20Mar%202021_1615237548.pdf.

- The Americas region reported 45.9% of daily case numbers and 64.5% of the daily deaths reported in the past 24 hours and maintained its position as the most severely affected region, having reported more than 51.69 million cases. Brazil reported 69 609 cases followed by the USA (57 269). 9 additional countries reported more than 1000 cases in the past 24 hours (Peru, Mexico, Chile, Colombia, Argentina, Canada, Ecuador, Paraguay, and Uruguay), and an additional 6 countries (Cuba, Panama, Jamaica, Bolivia, Dominican Republic, and Venezuela) reported more than 500 but fewer than 1000 cases.

- The European region reported 33.1% of daily case numbers and 23.2% of the daily deaths reported in the past 24 hours, and total cumulative cases reported exceed 39.89 million. Countries not reporting cases include Spain, Belgium, Sweden, Switzerland, Austria, and Kazakhstan, among others. France is dominant reporting over 21 600 cases in the last 24 hours, followed by Italy, Turkey, and Russia, reporting more than 10 000 new cases in the past 24 hours. Another 13 countries reported more than 1000 cases, and an additional 5 countries reported more than 500 but fewer than 1000 cases.

- The Eastern Mediterranean region reported 9.4% of daily case numbers and 5.8% of the deaths reported in the past 24 hours, having reported a cumulative total of more than 6.65 million cases. Iran maintains its dominance, reporting just over 8000 cases, followed by Jordan, Iraq, UAE, Lebanon, Palestinian Authority, Pakistan, Libya, Kuwait, and Oman, reporting more than 1000 cases. Tunisia and Egypt reported more than 500 but fewer than 1000 cases.

- The African region reported 2.5% of daily case numbers and 2.0% of the deaths reported in the past 24 hours, having reported a cumulative total of more than 2.90 million cases. Cameroon reported 3274 and Ethiopia reported 1109 cases. South Africa reported 862 cases. Botswana and Mauritania, among others, did not report any new cases in the past 24 hours.

- The Western Pacific region reported 1.8% of daily case numbers and 1.3% of the deaths reported in the past 24 hours, having reported a cumulative total of more than 1.66 million cases. Philippines reported the highest number of cases over the last 24 hours (approaching 3300 cases), followed by Malaysia, Japan, South Korea, and Mongolia.

- The South East Asia region reported 7.2% of the daily newly reported cases and 3.3% of reported deaths in the past 24 hours, having reported a cumulative total of more than 13.71 million cases. India is dominant, reporting 18 599 cases, followed by Indonesia (5826 cases), Bangladesh, Sri Lanka, and Maldives.

On the Overview tab at the WHO source URL, the epidemic curve of confirmed COVID-19 cases by WHO region, 30 Dec 2019 through 8 Mar 2021, is an excellent visual representation of the pandemic. - Mod.MPP]

