[In the past 24 hours, the USA (48 402), and Brazil (36 136), have reported the highest numbers of cases. A global total of 7249 deaths were reported in the past 24 hours (late 7 Mar 2021 to late 8 Mar 2021). Countries reporting more than 10 000 newly confirmed cases in the past 24 hours (7 countries) include the USA, Brazil, India (15 353), Italy (13 882), Turkey (13 215), Spain (11 958), and Russia (10 253). A total of 49 countries reported more than 1000 cases in the past 24 hours; 23 of the 49 countries are from the European region, 10 are from the Americas region, 9 are from the Eastern Mediterranean region, 2 are from the South East Asia region, 3 are from the Western Pacific region, and 2 from the African region.

Comparing the 7-day averages of daily confirmed cases from the past 7 days and those from 8-14 days ago, case counts have increased by 1.0%, while daily reported deaths have decreased by 3.9%. Similar comparative 7-day averages in the USA show an 11.8% decrease in daily reported cases and a 22.1% decrease in reported deaths.

Impression: Weekend artifact still present. The global daily reported cases totaled over 313 000 newly confirmed infections in the past 24 hours with over 117.74 million cumulative reported cases and over 2.61 million reported deaths. - Mod.MPP]
